creator: Dominik Gyecsek
descriptionHtml:
3000 words are all you need to easily express yourself and have everyday conversations in a language. This app has all the most common French ones, always available on your phone, even while offline.
60000 example sentences to put words into context, with pronunciations
Filter by Levels (A1, A2, B1, B2), Topics, Top 100 Groups, and Parts of Speech
Study without even opening the app, even on your watch, with flexibly scheduled notifications
Flashcard autoplay and auto-pronounce loops over your flashcards for times when you cannot use your hands
Practice with your favorite quiz types to master all words
descriptionShort: Study the Most Common 3000 Words with Examples to Learn French

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Fixed quiz card positioning
Fixed a bug where the ordering of sets was based on commonness instead of the last review date 
Extended daily goal history insight, so now you can see all your reviews on a calendar, with an export option
Floating progress bar every time you review a card, until you reach your daily goal
Added an option to see all example sentences from quiz practices as well
